data.content:
The root cause is that `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` 10.0 upgraded from **Microsoft.OpenApi v1** to **v2**, which has major breaking changes. Here are the four issues and their fixes:

---

### 1. `OpenApiString` / `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` removed
The entire `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` namespace (including `OpenApiString`, `OpenApiInteger`, etc.) is gone. `Example` is now `JsonNode?`.

```csharp
// Before
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// After
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

---

### 2. `Reference` property removed from model types
In v2, model classes no longer have a `Reference` property. Use the dedicated reference type instead.

```csharp
// Before
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
{
    Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
};

// After
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
```

---

### 3. `OpenApiSecurityRequirement` is no longer a dictionary
It no longer inherits `Dictionary<OpenApiSecurityScheme, IList<string>>`. Use its `Schemes` property instead.

```csharp
// Before
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
};

// After
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new()
    {
        Schemes = new Dictionary<OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference, IList<string>>
        {
            [oAuthScheme] = scopes
        }
    }
};
```

---

### 4. `Nullable` property removed
OpenAPI 3.1 (which v2 targets) expresses nullability via the `type` array, not a separate `nullable` keyword. `Type` is now a `JsonSchemaType` flags enum.

```csharp
// Before
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// After
property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

---

### Full corrected code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new()
        {
            Schemes = new Dictionary<OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference, IList<string>>
            {
                [oAuthScheme] = scopes
            }
        }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

The `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;` directive can be removed entirely.
